Celfin Plans Capital Increase for Expansions, CEO Tells Segunda

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-02-11T19:22:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/celfin-plans-capital-increase-for-expansions-ceo-tells-segunda.html
Celfin Capital SA, a Santiago-based
financial services firm, plans a $30 million to $40 million
capital increase this year for expansions in Latin America,  La
Segunda  reported.  The funds will come from partner contributions and retained
profits, Chief Executive Officer Alejandro Montero told the
afternoon newspaper in an interview.  Celfin aims to triple its size in five years, expanding in
asset management, brokerage services and private and investment
banking, La Segunda reported.  The firm expects to receive a license to operate in  Colombia  soon, while in  Peru  itâ€™s part of a consortium handling
a planned public offering of shares in state electricity
distributor Distriluz, Montero was quoted as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
